  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Operating envelope explicitly bounded: axial compressive force 0–2500 N, bending moment 0–25 N·m, screw outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm, construct length 100–130 mm, cortical bone surrogate density 0.32 g/cm³ ± 5%.",
